properties.Name: LifeInsurancePolicyFraud
properties.Description:
Fraudulent activities associated with the Insurance Policy.

Fraud is an act of deception, misstatement, misrepresentation of a material face made knowingly with the ultimate intention being to expose the Insurer to potential loss or suffer a potential financial hardship.

Columns.Name: InsurancePolicyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Policy.

Columns.Name: FraudReportedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Fraud was reported date.

Columns.Name: LifeInsuranceFraudTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Fraud Type.

Columns.Name: FraudCommittedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Fraud was committed date.

Columns.Name: PolicyContestedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Insured contested the policy because of the related fraud.

Columns.Name: PolicyVoidedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Insured voided the policy because of the related fraud.

Columns.Name: PolicyReissuanceDate
Columns.Description:
The date that the Insured reissued a new policy taking into account the fraud type activity.

For example, a new Insurance Policy based upon the correct age of the Insured may be issued.

Columns.Name: FraudNote
Columns.Description: Notes, comments or additional information regarding the Fraud.
